Last week Paul Scholes questioned the culture of golden caps and glass cabinets when England players make their 100th international appearance.

‘What does 100 caps mean?’ he asked. ‘Did you win something? No.’

Frank Lampard didn’t win anything with England - other than the player of the year awards in 2004 and 2005 - but 106 caps is an exceptional achievement.

