He worked too hard, motivated throughout his career by the words of a former West Ham team-mate when he was doing extra sets of ‘doggies’ after training.

‘What the **** are you doing?’ shouted Martyn Mullen, getting a laugh out of the young players for saying it. Where are they now?

Lampard is a proud Englishman. He wishes the famed golden generation could have won a major tournament. Perhaps David Beckham, Ashley Cole, John Terry, Gary Neville, Nicky Butt, Michael Owen, Wayne Rooney, Scholes, Gerrard and Lampard could have done more. They certainly had the talent.

